Body oblong, moderately compressed. Head large, its length greater than body depth. Eye very small, 6.9% (7.5–8.7%, mean 7.8%) of head length, covered with thick adipose eyelid; longitudinal length of adipose eyelid more than half of upper-jaw length. Anterior nostril and posterior nostril very similar in size. Maxilla covered with scales; lower lips well developed. Teeth villiform, in broad bands on vomer, palatines and ectopterygoids; tooth band of upper jaw wider than that of lower jaw; tooth band of upper jaw wider than width of space separating tooth bands on opposing premaxilla; length of palatine plate longer than that of ectopterygoid plate. Preopercular margin serrated. All pectoral-fin rays unbranched. First pectoral filament not reaching posterior tip of depressed pelvic fin; second filament extending beyond posterior tip of depressed pelvic fin, but not reaching posterior end of anal-fin base; third filament reaching (just short of in two 
paratypes
) middle of caudal peduncle; fourth filament extending slightly beyond caudal-fin base; fifth filament just reaching (extending slightly beyond in two 
paratypes
) caudal-fin base; sixth filament subequal to third filament. Scales covering entire body and head, except for lips and adipose eyelid.
